Section 2A. Monetary policy 
objectives

The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve 
System and the Federal Open Market Committee shall maintain 
long run growth of the monetary and credit aggregates commensurate with the economy's long run potential to increase
production, so as to promote effectively the goals of maximum employment, stable 
prices, and moderate long-term interest rates.

[12 USC 225a. As 
added by act of November 16, 1977 (91 Stat. 1387) and amended by acts of October 27,
1978 (92 Stat. 1897); Aug. 23, 1988 (102 Stat. 1375); and Dec. 27, 2000 (114 Stat. 3028).
